12 SAPS members stationed at the OR Tambo International Airport have been arrested. This follows a three-year joint investigation by the Hawks and Crime Intelligence that uncovered corruption by 17 police officials. JOHANNESBURG - 12 members of the SA Police Service, stationed at the OR Tambo International Airport, have been arrested. The arrest follows a three-year joint investigation by the Hawks and Crime Intelligence that uncovered corruption by 17 SAPS officials. READ: Policing facing new challenges, says Cele Out of the five others involved, three are expected to hand themselves over to the Kempton Park police station in the presence of their lawyers. One suspect remains at large and one is in quarantine.